AGENT HoneypotZone
VERSION 0.1
TRUST_LEVEL 3
PURPOSE Controlled observation zone that allows detected attacks to continue under monitoring,
     capturing polymorphic variants and attack chain behavior before constitutional kill
GOAL Observe attack behavior in a sandboxed zone to capture polymorphic variants,
     measure time-to-kill and constitutional distance at entry, and produce signed
     HoneypotCapture records for immune memory enrichment

RECEIVES attack_vec: List[float], payload: str, payload_variant: str
EMITS HoneypotCapture
MUTATES axiom_honeypot_log.jsonl
CANNOT_MUTATE trust_level, isolation, zone_distance_floor, observation_timeout_s

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 3 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ISOLATION is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ZONE_DISTANCE_FLOOR is 0.01 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT OBSERVATION_TIMEOUT_S is 30 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT Observation mode must be explicitly entered and exited
CONSTRAINT All captures are HMAC-SHA256 signed over canonical fields
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT Timeout triggers automatic kill to prevent observation escape

RULES
- On enter: set observation_mode True and start timer
- On observe: record polymorphic variant to attack chain
- On observe: if elapsed time exceeds OBSERVATION_TIMEOUT_S then auto kill
- On kill: set observation_mode False
- On kill: compute HMAC-SHA256 signature over canonical capture fields
- On kill: append signed capture as JSON line to axiom_honeypot_log.jsonl
- On kill: emit HoneypotCapture with all fields populated

PROCESS
- Guard detects attack at constitutional distance below ZONE_DISTANCE_FLOOR
- HoneypotZone.enter is called with attack vector and initial payload
- Observation mode activates and timer starts
- Subsequent payload variants are recorded via observe
- On explicit kill or timeout the zone captures all observations
- HoneypotCapture is HMAC signed and logged
- Capture data feeds into FixPlaybook for immune memory enrichment

CHECK
- enter sets observation_mode to True
- observe records variant in attack chain
- kill returns HoneypotCapture with signature
- kill sets observation_mode to False
- timeout triggers automatic kill
- ZONE_DISTANCE_FLOOR assignment raises AttributeError
- OBSERVATION_TIMEOUT_S assignment raises AttributeError

FAILURE
- On kill without prior enter: raise RuntimeError
- On observe without active observation: raise RuntimeError
- On log file write error: log warning but complete kill

CONCEPT AttackObservation
PURPOSE Monitor attack behavior in controlled zone to capture polymorphic variants
APPLIES WHEN attack detected near constitutional boundary and observation is valuable
NOT WHEN attack is IMMEDIATE_FAILURE severity requiring instant kill
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES active observation zone with timer
EFFECT Polymorphic attack chain captured for immune memory

OUTPUT
- HoneypotCapture with attack_chain, polymorphic_variants, time_to_kill_ms, signature

SUCCESS
observation_captures_variants:    0.25
timeout_triggers_auto_kill:       0.20
hmac_signature_valid:             0.20
observation_mode_lifecycle:       0.15
cannot_mutate_enforced:           0.10
log_append_correct:               0.10
